

     
      BEA is expected to announce today that they will open major parts of  WebLogic Workshop and donate it to the open source community in an attempt  to stop losing market share against for example JBoss which is a free  alternative to BEA's more expensive WebLogic licensing and support  programs.   With its code name "Beehive," BEA's global goal is to make the WebLogic  Development Framework the world's leading toolset for developing  applications - against competitors IBM, JBoss, and Oracle.  [Resource-Type: Weblink/News; Category: Java/J2EE/App Server]
     
    
